<br>
This bugs me.  A lot.  I'm obsessive about having all my spells.  I have every pet, every obscure spell -- stuff like Shard of the Core or Bandoleer of Luclin that took me months to find or find someone selling.  This if the first time that I haven't had every spell to scribe when I hit the level.<br>
<br>
In two months, I've found two people selling Burnout IV.  Both were level 60 clerics, and both wanted in excess of ten thousand platinum pieces for the spell.  Both laughed when I offered less.<br>
<br>
The thing that irks me is that the spell SUCKS.  It is marginally better than Burnout 3; the only reason it costs more is because it is rarer than hell.<br>
<br>
This bugs me because it is a harbinger of things to come.  At 56, the two best spells are both dropped, and at least one of them is as rare as Burnout IV.  <br>
<br>
I want to level more, to make 60, but I don't have 30k to buy three spells for the next two levels.  I don't even have the means to make 30k.  There's no point in being a level 60 mage if I can't perform the abilities associated with it.<br>
<br>
So how the hell do I get these spells?  It's really starting to piss me off now that I am being held up by it.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts at all would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
-nid <p><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#BBBBBB">
<b>Niden Shadowhand</b><br>
55 Conjurer, Drinal
